.\" Manpage for SimpleShell
.TH SIMPLESHELL 1 "August 2025" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
SimpleShell \- a minimal shell to run commands and view environment variables
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simpleshell
[\fICOMMAND\fR ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
SimpleShell is a lightweight shell that can execute commands found in the system PATH or by absolute path, and provides two built-in commands: \fBexit\fR and \fBenv\fR.
.PP
It does not support advanced shell features such as pipes, I/O redirection, or background execution.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env
Displays the current environment variables.
.TP
.B external commands
Any executable in the PATH or specified with an absolute path can be run with arguments.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run a command in PATH:
.RS
($) ls -l
.RE
Display environment variables:
.RS
($) env
.RE
Exit the shell:
.RS
($) exit
.RE
.SH LIMITATIONS
.PP
- No support for pipes (\fB|\fR) or I/O redirection (\fB>\fR, \fB<\fR)  
- No background execution (\fB&\fR)  
- Only one command per line  
- No scripting support or shell expansions
.SH AUTHOR
Written by Adel Mejrissi.
